\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s23 \f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \s23\fi-360\li648\ri288\keep\nowidctlpar\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls2\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\i Speed}{: the speed, in ft/s, at which the object will move.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s23 \f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \s23\fi-360\li648\ri288\keep\nowidctlpar\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls2\adjustright {\i Pause}{: the amount of time, in ms, that the object should pause at the "from" node of this link.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s23 \f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \s23\fi-360\li648\ri288\keep\nowidctlpar\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls2\adjustright {\i Path limit?}{: whether you want the object to be limited rigidly to the path or not by the "from" node.  Objects which are not path limited have smoother, more momentum-like movement, but can stray from their paths by an amount proportional to their speed.
